ce-name=\"Volkswagen\" data-title=\"VW ID.Buzz\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-full-height=\"1334\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NjMxNDM4/vw-idbuzz-seats.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02ead891f000264e\" data-image-slug=\"VW ID.Buzz seats\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NjMxNDM4\" data-source-name=\"Volkswagen\" data-title=\"VW ID.Buzz\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cphx-gallery-image data-full-height=\"1334\" data-full-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_2000%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_2000/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1OTAy/vw-idbuzz-steering.jpg\" data-full-width=\"2000\" data-image-id=\"ci02ead891f00024cc\" data-image-slug=\"VW ID.Buzz steering\" data-public-id=\"MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1OTAy\" data-source-name=\"volkswagen\" data-source-page-url=\"\"\u003e\u003c/phx-gallery-image\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/ar_16:9%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Ch_406%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzIzOTM1ODIy/vw-idbuzz-side.jpg\" alt=\"VW ID.Buzz side\" itemprop=\"image\" loading=\"lazy\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"there-are-lots-of-family-friendly-ev-alternatives\"\u003eThere are lots of family-friendly EV alternatives\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe ID.Buzz can currently tout that it’s the only electric minivan on the market. But does that really matter? Minivans are already a dying segment, and there are a whole mess of SUVs that are more affordable and better performers than the ID.Buzz. \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/kia/\"\u003eKia\u003c/a\u003e’s three-row EV9 starts at around the same price as the ID.Buzz and holds the same number of passengers, while offering 70 miles more of range in the Light Long Range RWD version. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/news/view-photos-of-the-2025-vw-id-buzz\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Rear three-quarters of the new bus.\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMzI0MDAxMzU4/vw-idbuzz-rear.jpg\" height=\"5239\" width=\"7855\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003eRear three-quarters of the new bus.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eVolkswagen\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eAnd if, by chance, you aren’t looking to take advantage of the van’s seven-seater capabilities, the many mainstays in the electric SUV segment all offer dramatically better value. \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/tesla-model-y-review\"\u003eTesla Model Y\u003c/a\u003e offers 100 miles more range and similar straight-line speed. Luxury brands like Mercedes-Benz even offer more affordable solutions, like the Mercedes-Benz EQB – which tops out at around where the ID.Buzz starts. It’s a similar story with vehicles like the Hyundai IONIQ 5 and even the \u003ca href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/2025-rivian-r1s-ev-suv-pros-and-cons\"\u003eRivian R1S\u003c/a\u003e and Model X aren’t far from the top-trim price point. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-picture\u003e\u003ca\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.webp 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.webp 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.webp 700w\"/\u003e\u003csource sizes=\"(min-width: 1240px) 700px, (min-width: 675px) 620px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-srcset=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_380/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.jpg 380w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_620/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.jpg 620w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.jpg 700w\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Looking into the past, perhaps?\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/t_share/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.jpg\" data-src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/c_limit%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:good%2Cw_700/MjEwMjE4NDUyMDU1NTY1NTE2/vw-idbuzz.jpg\" height=\"5360\" width=\"8036\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" itemprop=\"contentUrl url\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/phoenix-picture\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"caption\"\u003eLooking into the past, perhaps?\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp itemprop=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eVolkswagen\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eWe’ll admit: there is no direct competitor for the ID.Buzz. If you are only shopping for a fully-electric minivan – and nothing else – you’ve found your vehicle. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eOtherwise, choosing to buy one is an emotional decision based on (admittedly pretty cool) looks and lifestyle. And while there’s nothing wrong with that, it may have been an easier ask if the van’s pricing was at least remotely enticing. The original Type 2 Microbus was a success thanks to its relative simplicity, affordability, and space. The new one appears to be coasting. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cphoenix-super-link href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/features/aptly-named-peace-vans-ready-to-build-the-2025-id-buzz-youre-looking-for\" onclick=\"return window.phoenixTrackClickEvent(this, event);\" phx-track-id=\"Embed Card Click\"\u003e\u003c/phoenix-super-link\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/article\u003e\u003c/section\u003e\u003csection id=\"phximagetilehub-3\"\u003e\u003cphoenix-hub data-group-size=\"9\" 